NASB - English.11:
11Then Judah said to his daughter-in-law Tamar, “Remain a widow in your father’s house until my son Shelah grows up”;
for he thought, “I am afraid that he too may die like his brothers.”
So Tamar went and lived in her father’s house.

NASB - English.16:
16So he turned aside to her by the road, and said, “Here now, let me have relations with you”;
for he did not know that she was his daughter-in-law.
And she said, “What will you give me, that you may have relations with me?”

